[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_tujd8")
ref_name = "Hubble Space Telescope"
ref_desc = "[b][color=light_blue]Section:[/color] 3[/b]
The Hubble Space Telescope was launched into low-Earth orbit in 1990. After some initial troubles with the primary mirror having a manufacturing flaw and many servicing missions it is still operational to this day.
It uses a Ritchey-Chrétien version of the Cassegrain telescope design with a primary mirror and a secondary mirror, feeding the light through a hole in the primary mirror towards the back of the telescope.
It contains 4 major instruments, which are:
• Advanced Camera for Surveys 
• Wide Field Camera 3
• Space Telescope Imaging 
• Cosmic Origins Spectrograph
The telescope mostly operates in visible light, but can also work in near UV and near IR."
wavelength_low = 90.0
wavelength_high = 2400.0
metadata/_custom_type_script = "uid://chyrk1ts4wb7h"
